            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prompt Rollout"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A prompt rollout is the staged migration of live traffic from one prompt version to the next. Unlike a code deploy, a prompt change is invisible to the infrastructure — the same model, the same hardware, only the instruction changes. This means you cannot rely on standard deployment canaries (error rate, 500s) to catch problems; you need LLM-specific quality signals."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rolling out in stages — shadow, 5%, 25%, 100% — limits the blast radius of a bad prompt change to a small fraction of users while you collect enough production samples to make a statistically confident decision."
          }
        ]
      },
