      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Shadow mode runs the new prompt in parallel with the old one on every request, discards the new prompt's output, and logs both responses for offline comparison. It surfaces problems at zero risk before any user sees the new prompt."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Traffic Routing Implementation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Route traffic by hashing the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "user_id",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " — users see a consistent prompt version across sessions (conversation coherence). Do not hash on "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "session_id",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for prompt rollouts; a mid-conversation prompt switch changes the assistant's behavior and breaks continuity."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import hashlib\nfrom your_module import load_prompt, flag_store\n\ndef select_prompt(name: str, user_id: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    Read canary percentage from feature flag store,\n    route deterministically by user_id.\n    \"\"\"\n    canary_pct = float(flag_store.get(f\"prompt_canary_pct_{name}\", default=\"0\"))\n    bucket = int(hashlib.sha256(user_id.encode()).hexdigest(), 16) % 100\n\n    if bucket < canary_pct:\n        return load_prompt(name, stage=\"Staging\")   # candidate\n    return load_prompt(name, stage=\"Production\")    # current\n\n# Advancing the rollout — called by CI after each gate passes:\n# flag_store.set(\"prompt_canary_pct_rag-assistant\", \"5\")    # start canary\n# flag_store.set(\"prompt_canary_pct_rag-assistant\", \"25\")   # advance\n# flag_store.set(\"prompt_canary_pct_rag-assistant\", \"100\")  # full rollout\n# Then promote candidate to Production in the registry, remove flag."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Shadow Mode Implementation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Shadow mode fires both prompts in parallel. The old prompt's response is returned to the user; the new prompt's response is discarded but logged. Compare the logs offline to compute judge scores and latency deltas before committing to even a 5% canary:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio, anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nasync def shadow_run(\n    user_id: str,\n    query: str,\n    context: list[str],\n    trace_logger,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Run old and new prompts in parallel.\n    Return the old prompt's response; log both for comparison.\n    \"\"\"\n    old_prompt = load_prompt(\"rag-assistant\", stage=\"Production\")\n    new_prompt = load_prompt(\"rag-assistant\", stage=\"Staging\")\n\n    old_msgs = build_messages(old_prompt, query, context)\n    new_msgs = build_messages(new_prompt, query, context)\n\n    old_resp, new_resp = await asyncio.gather(\n        call_llm_async(old_msgs, old_prompt[\"parameters\"]),\n        call_llm_async(new_msgs, new_prompt[\"parameters\"]),\n    )\n\n    trace_logger.log({\n        \"user_id\": user_id,\n        \"old_version\": old_prompt[\"version\"],\n        \"new_version\": new_prompt[\"version\"],\n        \"old_response\": old_resp,\n        \"new_response\": new_resp,   # discarded; logged for eval\n        \"mode\": \"shadow\",\n    })\n\n    return old_resp  # users only see this\n\nasync def call_llm_async(messages: list, params: dict) -> str:\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=params[\"max_tokens\"],\n        temperature=params[\"temperature\"],\n        messages=messages,\n    )\n    return response.content[0].text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Gate Checks"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Automated gates decide whether to advance the rollout. A gate runner checks the last N minutes of traces and computes key metrics. If any gate fails, the flag reverts to the previous stage:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# scripts/prompt_gate.py\nimport json, statistics\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\n\ndef load_traces(name: str, version: str, lookback_minutes: int = 30) -> list[dict]:\n    \"\"\"Load recent traces for a given prompt version from trace store.\"\"\"\n    cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(minutes=lookback_minutes)\n    # Implementation depends on your trace store (DynamoDB, BigQuery, etc.)\n    return trace_store.query(prompt_name=name, version=version, since=cutoff)\n\ndef check_gate(name: str, candidate_version: str, current_version: str) -> bool:\n    candidate_traces = load_traces(name, candidate_version)\n    current_traces   = load_traces(name, current_version)\n\n    if len(candidate_traces) < 30:\n        print(f\"Insufficient samples: {len(candidate_traces)} (need ≥ 30)\")\n        return False\n\n    # Latency gate: candidate p95 must not exceed current p95 by more than 10%\n    candidate_p95 = statistics.quantiles(\n        [t[\"latency_ms\"] for t in candidate_traces], n=20)[18]  # 95th percentile\n    current_p95 = statistics.quantiles(\n        [t[\"latency_ms\"] for t in current_traces], n=20)[18]\n    if candidate_p95 > current_p95 * 1.10:\n        print(f\"FAIL latency: candidate p95={candidate_p95:.0f}ms > current*1.10={current_p95*1.10:.0f}ms\")\n        return False\n\n    # Quality gate: candidate judge score must not drop below threshold\n    candidate_quality = statistics.mean([t[\"judge_score\"] for t in candidate_traces])\n    QUALITY_THRESHOLD = 0.85\n    if candidate_quality < QUALITY_THRESHOLD:\n        print(f\"FAIL quality: judge={candidate_quality:.3f} < {QUALITY_THRESHOLD}\")\n        return False\n\n    print(f\"PASS: p95={candidate_p95:.0f}ms, judge={candidate_quality:.3f}\")\n    return True"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "CI Pipeline for Prompt Rollout"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/prompt-rollout.yml\nname: prompt-rollout\non:\n  workflow_dispatch:\n    inputs:\n      prompt_name: { description: \"Prompt name\", required: true }\n      version:     { description: \"Candidate version (e.g. v9)\", required: true }\n\njobs:\n  shadow:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - name: Enable shadow mode\n        run: |\n          python scripts/set_flag.py \\\n            --flag \"prompt_canary_pct_${{ inputs.prompt_name }}\" \\\n            --value \"0\"\n          python scripts/set_flag.py \\\n            --flag \"prompt_shadow_${{ inputs.prompt_name }}\" \\\n            --value \"${{ inputs.version }}\"\n      - name: Wait for shadow samples\n        run: sleep 300  # 5 min; in practice run overnight\n\n  canary-5:\n    needs: shadow\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - name: Check shadow gate\n        run: |\n          python scripts/prompt_gate.py \\\n            --name ${{ inputs.prompt_name }} \\\n            --candidate ${{ inputs.version }} \\\n            --current production\n      - name: Advance to 5%\n        run: |\n          python scripts/set_flag.py \\\n            --flag \"prompt_canary_pct_${{ inputs.prompt_name }}\" \\\n            --value \"5\"\n      - name: Soak 30 min and gate\n        run: |\n          sleep 1800\n          python scripts/prompt_gate.py \\\n            --name ${{ inputs.prompt_name }} \\\n            --candidate ${{ inputs.version }} \\\n            --current production \\\n            --min-samples 50\n\n  full-rollout:\n    needs: canary-5\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: production    # requires manual approval\n    steps:\n      - name: Advance to 100%\n        run: |\n          python scripts/set_flag.py \\\n            --flag \"prompt_canary_pct_${{ inputs.prompt_name }}\" \\\n            --value \"100\"\n      - name: Promote in registry\n        run: |\n          python scripts/promote_prompt.py \\\n            --name ${{ inputs.prompt_name }} \\\n            --version ${{ inputs.version }} \\\n            --to-stage Production\n      - name: Clear rollout flags\n        run: |\n          python scripts/set_flag.py \\\n            --flag \"prompt_canary_pct_${{ inputs.prompt_name }}\" \\\n            --delete\n          python scripts/set_flag.py \\\n            --flag \"prompt_shadow_${{ inputs.prompt_name }}\" \\\n            --delete"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rollback During Rollout"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "If a gate fails at any stage, revert the flag to the previous stage value. The registry is not updated until full rollout, so rollback is purely a flag operation — no artifact change needed:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# rollback_prompt_rollout.py\nimport os\nfrom your_module import flag_store\n\ndef rollback_rollout(prompt_name: str, reason: str) -> None:\n    flag_key = f\"prompt_canary_pct_{prompt_name}\"\n    current = float(flag_store.get(flag_key, default=\"0\"))\n\n    if current >= 100:\n        # Full rollout already completed — use registry rollback instead\n        raise RuntimeError(\n            \"Rollout is complete. Use prompt registry rollback, not rollout rollback.\"\n        )\n    elif current >= 25:\n        target = 5.0\n    elif current >= 5:\n        target = 0.0\n    else:\n        target = 0.0\n\n    flag_store.set(flag_key, str(target))\n    print(f\"Rolled back {prompt_name}: {current}% → {target}% (reason: {reason})\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    rollback_rollout(\n        prompt_name=os.environ[\"PROMPT_NAME\"],\n        reason=os.environ.get(\"REASON\", \"gate failure\"),\n    )"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
