      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Special Case: Prompt Rollout with Fine-Tuned Adapters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When both the prompt and the adapter change together (a coordinated update), do not roll them out independently. A new prompt written for a new adapter may perform poorly on the old adapter, and vice versa. Roll them out as a unit:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Register both new prompt (v9) and new adapter (v15) as candidates together."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Shadow mode runs the full combination (v9 + adapter-v15) against the current combination (v8 + adapter-v14)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Canary traffic sees both changes simultaneously; rollback reverts both flags atomically."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "models.yaml",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " entry records the paired versions: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "{prompt: v9, adapter: v15}",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Never mix versions from different pairings in production — an eval score computed for (v9, adapter-v15) is not valid evidence that (v9, adapter-v14) is safe."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Prompt rollout is shadow → canary → full, gated on latency and judge-score signals at each step. Route by "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "user_id",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " for conversation coherence. Roll out prompt and adapter changes as a unit when they are coupled. Keep the registry uninvolved until 100% rollout is complete — rollback at any earlier stage is a pure flag operation."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
